---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - Avengh"
  description="Learn how Avengh protects your privacy and handles your data. Our privacy policy outlines our commitment to data security and user rights."
>
  <section class="timeline static-page" id="privacy">
      <h1 class="section-title">PRIVACY POLICY</h1>
      <div class="timeline-container">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-content glass">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>
              Welcome to Avengers Fist. We are committed to protecting your privacy
              and ensuring you have a positive experience on our website and in using
              our products and services.
            </p>
            <h2>Information Collection</h2>
            <p>
              We collect various types of information in connection with the services we provide, including:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Personal Data:</strong> Name, email address, contact details, etc.</li>
              <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Information about how our services are accessed and used.</li>
            </ul>
            <h2>Use of Information</h2>
            <p>We use the collected data to:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Provide and maintain our services</li>
              <li>Notify you about changes to our services</li>
              <li>Allow you to participate in interactive features</li>
              <li>Provide customer support</li>
              <li>Analyze usage to improve our services</li>
            </ul>
            <h2>Sharing of Information</h2>
            <p>We may share your information with:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Service providers to monitor and analyze the use of our service</li>
              <li>Affiliates for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy</li>
              <li>Legal authorities if required by law</li>
            </ul>
            <h2>Data Security</h2>
            <p>
              We use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal data, but remember that no method of
              transmission over the Internet is 100% secure.
            </p>
            <h2>User Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Access and update your personal data</li>
              <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
              <li>Object to processing of your data</li>
              <li>Request the portability of your data</li>
            </ul>
            <h2>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
            <p>
              We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to track the activity on our service and hold certain
              information. You can instruct your browser to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent.
            </p>
            <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>
              We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new
              Privacy Policy on this page.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
